{
  "doc_id": "2103",
  "text": "After that, [CITATION_1] presented a non-isolated modular dc/dc converter (MDCC) based on two chains of submodules (SMs). Thanks to one stage conversion, it offers the reduced number of the SMs, and gets rid of the full-rated ac transformer. Thus, the MDCC provides a low-cost solution for the interconnection of HVDC systems with low or medium voltage stepping ratio [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . However, a relatively large sine-wave modulated ac circulating current is introduced to keep the charge balance of the SM capacitors [CITATION_4] , which increases the power loss. To resolve the problem, the MDCC with the stepped 2-level modulation (S2L-MDCC), whose operation principle is similar with that of the conventional buck converter, was presented in [CITATION_5] . Compared with the sine-wave modulated MDCCs, the S2L-MDCC offers the merits of smaller ac circulating current and higher efficiency.",
